<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-04-18T16:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-04-18T16:45:00-05:00" n="880" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d880">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00 Bandit Activities, 1931/43:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Vice Consul at Bluefields</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Rowe</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bluefields</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-04-18T16:00:00-05:45">April 18, 1931—4
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In view of repeated rumors of threatened bandit attack upon El Gallo, the
                            Fruit Company Station, 3 officers and 27 enlisted Guardia are being sent
                            there, leaving 3 officers and 13 Guardia in Bluefields. One officer and
                            30 enlisted Marines from U.S.S. <hi rend="italic">Sacramento</hi> are
                            being landed at Bluefields today to assure order in the absence of
                            Guardia.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Rowe</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>